description:
To begin with there is no taste of  “authentic Mangalorean food” but just the menu. I visited with my friends for lunch with great excitement assuming it is authentic mangalorean (the name kudla misled us).
Ambiance is good, ppl at the restaurant kind and helpful.
We ordered mangalore goli bajje (was good) chicken ghee roast (there was hardly any ghee in it, it was pure chilli masala, the meat was frozen n tasteless), mutton sukka (average), kori rotti (abv average, again chkn meat frozen), neer dosa (average), butter milk (good),& pepper panner (good).
The price range is ok but calling it as authentic Mangalorean is inappropriate. They have lot to improve on taste and fresh Ingredients (meat especially).
So people who want to try, surely u can but lower ur expectation. I don’t think i will ever visit. This assessment is based on me as a Mangalorean & food is no match to my native.
Pathetic service
Ok

While the food is reasonably priced and taste above satisfactory, the service is appalling. Nobody bothers to come offer a menu till much later; the tables are not clean, and they take forever to serve the dishes - one each time. This is a Sun evening btw with hardly any other customers around.

Pretty pathetic place in terms of customer service! Went there on 27 Apr with friends. We ordered mutton and chicken biryani one each. The guy returned after 20 min to tell that chicken biryani is not available and can you change to mutton biryani instead which we agreed to. He returned again after around 3-4 min and said can you change again, we don't have mutton biryani and have only 1 chicken biryani. What really got us irritated was that just a few min ago he had mentioned that chicken Biryani is finished and then it magically appeared. We decided to cancel our order and return without having our lunch
Ambience - Bad
Food - Did not taste
Customer service - Pathetic

Pros : Food was good
Order A la carte
Booze all enjoyed

Cons : Service was not good , Couldn handle the crowd on Friday eve
People who ordered buffet are the losers

If you think you can invite 30 pax by ordering for 28 pax it’s definetly the wrong place

You have to order for 30 pax and invite 15 pax

And since ours was a bad experience am letting you all know

(The quantity was insufficient for big appetites )

That 1 start is because the food was decent couldn’t resist giving a star

As of June 2024, restaurant management has changed and is moving away from Mangalorean cuisine. There still are a few Mangaloreaan dishes like pulimunchi, neer dosa that can still be ordered, but taste is slightly different from the authentic stuff.

Authentic Mangalore Food is still not here! I went thinking of relishing the dishes that I love,  although food is decent it is no where even slightly close to a good mangalorean food. Ordered neer dosa, Chicken Ghee Roast (totally incorrect dish) and Goli Baje. Average taste, but affordable price.
Really nice place, but little bit noisy (it's usual one)
May improve the quality of the time

First visit with an open mind to try unfamiliar dishes and the waiter suggested 3 dishes based on our preference :

1) Murgh Anarkali Tikka $15 (7/10 bit over charred corners),
2) Chicken Milagu Masala $11 (7.5/10 loved it until next dish..),
3) Methi Chicken Masala $12 (8.5/10 so gd ordered twice)

we also added :
Garlic Nann $4.7ea x 2 (9/10 so gd ordered twice)
and Mutton Dum Briyani $14 (7/10 for comparison)

The Methi Chic and Nann were was goood...we encored despite being satisfied and full already.

Portion and prices are reasonable. Went in for early dinner, service was okay.

But pls update your google address, we went to upper weld rd on a rainy day to only discover you've moved to Norris Rd.

Def will going back for Methi Chic Masala and Nann (let it sit until slightly drier for best texture/taste)
Worst service...one person had to leave because they took more than an hour to give veg meal.
Food was good from non vegetarian perspective. For a vegetarian, it an avg food and limited options.
The food was great!!! Must try the mutton

A good restaurant in the CBP area. The food was good but they should try to maintain the outer seating areas.
Great rooftop kitchen and bar. Staffs are friendly. And food is good with real Indian taste. Recommend Kal dosa and pepper mushroom fry.

Good place to hang out for Indian cuisine. It's a bar attached garden restaurent on roof top. As the dinner was arranged for the whole office and project team, we booked the whole restaurant. We had chance to have the buffet which included all kind of north Indian dishes. Good authentic indian food. Ambience is good.
Good beer and awesome curry. Will def be back!
Authentic Punjabi food, Ghar ka khana
If you go early, will get seats inside. Average hotel in the locality. Drinks price seems to be on higher side
I was craving for mangalore food, at-last found one in Singapore, must visit restaurant, you get all mangalore cuisine here, I want to visit again.
Another hidden gem. Good choice of drinks and food.

Kudla village was a complete surprise for me. Never experienced a feel good factor away from home. The restaurant took us back to kudla, Mangalore...  Ms Jothi and Mr Poorna were top notch in their service. The chef met us in person and walked us through the menu even though we were familiar with most of the dishes. This review is posted after our 3rd visit in the last 5days. We walk from Bencoolen to Norris road in Little India to enjoy our dinner. Completely satisfied with the food, ambience and the service. Perfect Mangalore delight.

It’s a new place . Food is quite authentic and good . But service has to speed up . Also it would be great if the waiters don’t keep staring at the diners as they eat . That’s not the way to gauge if customer likes the food . It’s uncomfortable.

Found this place luckily on google.. Fantastic food! True Mangalorean style. Kaane Fish Rawa fry & Anjal tawa fry must try! Chicken Ghee roast is out of this world.. All in all a must visit restaurant.
Good food. Amazing friendly staff and open ambience - just what you need at the end of a long day. Limited menu but everything available is good and quick.

The best part was the AC. Service was terrible. I finished my meal and waited over 45 minutes and had to leave since the food never came out for my husband. Butter chicken was also alright, I’ve definitely had better. Save yourself the trip and go somewhere else.
One of the best places I’ve eaten on Little India, Great Food, awesome.
Lokasinya deket bugis, asiknya datang sore supaya gak panas.
I just ordered Mutton biriyani from this restaurant via Foodpanda. There was 3 miserably small pieces of mutton in a mound of rice!! What a scam! Never ever ordering from this restaurant again!
Amazing varieties, awesome taste. You want to try Indian traditional food, this is THE place.

A cuisine close to heart, unfortunately missing in Singapore - Mangalorean food!!! That changed completely today.. I would now say - look no further beyond “Kudla Village” restaurant @ Norris Road. Let me begin with service. We felt at home. Such a lovely warm bunch of people who literally took us back to Mangalore.

If service (for some reason) could’nt remind of Mangalore,  the food definitely…. Blindfolded I can say couldn’t spot a difference of having delicious Mangalorean food in mangalore or in singapore. The food is to die for and took us straight to Mangalore. Right from Buns, to prawns ghee roast to Kori roti and finally Gadbad!!!!

In terms of recommendation, I would definitely visit back not once but quite quite often…

It was was raining earlier and we couldn't go the place we decided earlier for dinner which is 20km away from my home. Then I tried my luck in google maps and searched for restaurants nearby. There were many options but most of them were about to close,so we decided to go here in heritage one which is near to our home.
We order hot and sour soup 1/2, and 1 set prata to try the taste, the taste was beyond our expectations and we ordered 2 more set prata and pallippalayam chicken which was really delicious. Total bill for 2 person was under 40 we will go there again for sure. I will give 5 stars for the food atmosphere and their service.

Ps: North Indians may not be a big fan of seeragasamba rice, so may be try something different.

This place is relocated from Changi to little India and no longer roof top. However,

They are too specific nowadays. Only concentrate on some people (rich i think so) Service is more worse when compared to 2020. Don't want to give an example.. for their boss pls concentrate on service and respect. Tell your guys to give a glass of water when customer came and sit on the table. Pls tc hope u will change it

Pleased to see a Mangalorean restaurant finally opening up in Singapore. Decided to try this out on a weekday around 2PM.

The place was quite empty. The environs are clean and the staff is super friendly. We ordered the following :

1) Korri Rotti - I liked the gravy of the korri rotti, very similar to the one you get back home in Mangalore. The chicken, was a bit disappointing - chewy and seemed unfresh. Quantity was generous.

2) Anjal Tawa Fry - The masala for the tawa fry was really good, reminding me of home. The fish, however, didn't seem fresh.

3) Chicken Ghee Roast - Similar experience to the korri rotti and anjal tawa fry. Good masala and seasoning, but the chicken was too chewy and very little meat.

4) Buns - Took a take-away of Mangalore buns. Appropriately sweet and fluffy. Liked this.

5) Goli Bajje - Soft and crunchy golli bajje with coconut chutney.
Very poor Indian food. Would give 0 stars
Best place for a weekday drink in CBP... Starters were very good..

This is my 2nd visit with my family, and on both occasions had fish meal the buttermilk previous time was better but overall worth the order :), also had schezwan fried rice, gobi manchurian, kane rava fry, bangude masala fry,chicken lollipop, prawn ghee roast, goli baje, lassi and gadbad (mix from both visit) and each item took me straight to mangalore..so to all my mlore and non mlore frens out there who are keen to explore pls visit this place and iam sure u would also spend time and write an review like me..sorry forgot to take pics as was busy enjoying the food and a special shout out to staff who serve with a heart.

Was randomly walking in the area with my wife for groceries and chanced upon a sign for a rooftop restaurant. Curiosity got the better of me and it totally paid off!

The Biryani is to die for, it is spicy, it is so fragrant, it sits easily as one of the best bryanis I've eaten ever.

We also tried the butter chicken and Naan and we weren't disappointed. My wife is a lady that doesn't eat much and yet she finished up all the carbs available. That's a good sign. Will recommend, will come back again!

Was here with friends for a Sunday lunch and was unsure as it was a new establishment. After the dishes were served, must say we were totally happy with the awesome taste of the food. Friendly staff. A must try place for any South Indian cuisine lovers. Even vegetarians have very good option.

Loved this place. It was quite empty when we went in. We went there with our 4 month old baby. When our baby started crying, they took us to a smaller section which was non operational today to give us our privacy. All thanks to Mr. Purua Jyothi and other staff members.

Coming to the food , we ordered Golli Bhajje which was a nice starter.

For mains we ordered Paneer Ghee Roast. It was super spicy and it blew out socks off (in a good way). It was sooo tasty we just enjoyed it.
Neer dosa was super thin and yummy.

Do not miss the Gadbad ice-cream the end. An amazing treat after tasty food.

All in all a great experience service wise and food wise as well

Such a beautiful places and foods was served very nice delicious bar  bistro one of the most excellent service and warmest welcome place we had a good time with my colleagues there and tasty foods I need thanks to the management and team not forget to mention  venkat and madhu the waitress who served us with smiles 😀 😊 keep it
You can eat peacefully and relaxly.the server behaved very kindly. The drawback is they serve the food too late. But the taste is good.

Had a great dinner with my friends yesterday. We thoroughly enjoyed the food particularly Mutton Briyani and Sizzler, kudos to Chef (unknown).
Pros : Appetizing and scrumptious dishes, nice roof top in CBP,  highly relaxing ambience, friendly service.
Cons : very crowded during peak hours, but worth waiting.
Sugg: Better to reserve if you plan to go in group

I often came to heritage for drinks,side dishes and dinner with my friends.
On Aug 2023, I was so surprised about the bill.
Some of the food prices are increased and the Quantity reduced.
Example: onion pakkoda Qty reduced and price is not reasonable.
The taste, service and atmosphere are worth it.
High-class and Rich taste ,💯

My uncle called me up, excited to tell me about this mangalorean place in Singapore. We are from Namma kudla and to find out someone was dishing out authentic dishes in SG was a Godsend.
So with plans set, we visited this place. I have to admit I was nervous and excited. Excited to try our dishes and nervous on how it would taste.
We ordered all our local authentic dishes like Fish thali, Surmai tawa fry, chicken ghee roast, Kori rotti and Chicken gashi. We ended our feast with Gadbad and it was quite similar to Pabbas Gadbad from Mangalore.
The food was authentic, both to look at and to taste. We were so happy. The depth of flavor was perfect.
The staff were courteous and attentive and the food waiting time was less. Next time I feel the need for some Namma Kudla food, I know where to go :)

So far so in my visits there,  humble owner on the counter.

But its crowded on fridays as everyone on earth wants to hang around and they wont leave easily. Haha.
I have been here on weekends for several time. Nice place to relax and have fun with friends and enjoy good South Indian food. Service staffs are very friendly!

I have invited a 3 friends for the dinner.
The service is fantastic.
The food taste very tasty.
The portion is good enough.
The price is cheap.
The place near to the little India police station.

I was quite disappointed. We ordered chicken ghee, kori rotti, fish thali, and fish fry. The waiting time was not bad; the food arrived early. However, the chicken ghee roast tasted like chili chicken or something else, but definitely not like ghee roast at all. The kori rotti chicken curry was disappointing because the portion size was not sufficient for the rotti they provided, and the curry was thicker compared to authentic curry, which is usually runny for rotti. The extra curry was charged $2, but I was informed it would not come with any pieces, and the portion was very small in a tiny bowl.

As for the fish fry, the fish wasn't fresh, and it tasted like frozen fish. The fish meal came with curry, and I was told there wouldn't be any fish in the fish curry. While the prices were decent, the taste did not match authentic Mangalore cuisine.

Food was quite awful, nothing like Manglorean food, everything had a bitter taste, and the fish was obviously not fresh, very low quality cuisine. Women bathroom flush was not working and it was in horrible condition

Me and my wife had a lovely experience here. The food was great and most importantly the staff were really very warm , welcoming and friendly. My Dhaneswaran was great in his recommendations and we enjoyed this unique cuisine tremendously.  Great staff who make the place great too. Thank you all. Cheers

Food tastes good, after DTKR, I would say these guys have got the best seeraga samba Mutton Biryani. Mutton Biryani is full of flavour and the mutton is well cooked and is made in ghee so very aromatic. But the lower rating is because, they don't have proper chicken Biryani and they don't say that. they just pack a chicken piece in mutton biryani and send you away and if you have family members who don't like mutton, they can't eat the chicken biryani due to the mutton flavour and lot of small mutton pieces. And the chicken piece they put in the chicken Biryani is also dry and old. Not a good experience with takeaway..the mutton biryani like I said is a highlight. let's see next time.
